history massively multiplayer online role-playing games mmorpg term coined by richard garriott refer massive multiplayer online role-playing games their social communities link between garriott mmorpg term has been recognised by many scholars previous this related coinages these games were generally called graphical muds history mmorpgs traces back directly through mud genre through this connection mmorpgs can be seen have roots earliest multi-user games such mazewar mud1 saw release roguelike pseudo-graphical mud called island kesmai on compuserve lucasfilm's graphical mud habitat first fully graphical multi-user rpg was neverwinter nights which was delivered through america online was personally championed by aol president steve case other early proprietary graphical online rpgs include three on sierra network shadow yserbius fates twinion ruins cawdor another milestone came nsfnet restrictions were lifted opening internet up for game developers which allowed for first truly massively-scoped titles finally mmorpgs defined today began with meridian innovative both its scope offering first-person graphics with realm online appearing nearly simultaneously ultima online released often credited with first popularizing genre though more mainstream attention was garnered by 1999's everquest asheron's call west 1996's nexus kingdom winds south korea financial success these early titles has ensured competition genre since that time mmorpg titles now exist on consoles new settings current market for mmorpgs has blizzard entertainment's world warcraft dominating largest mmorpg alongside other titles such final fantasy xiv guild wars though additional market exists for free-to-play mmorpgs which are supported by advertising purchases in-game items this free-to-play model particularly common south korean mmorpgs such maplestory rohan blood feud atlantica online also there are some free-to-play games such runescape & tibia where game free but one would have pay monthly play gam